  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Business Development Executive (Wine)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role Mission:</strong></p><p>We are seeking a dynamic and results-driven <strong>Business Development Executive</strong> to join our growing team. This role involves expanding market presence, building strong business partnerships relationships, and collaborating with internal teams to deliver exceptional service and brand experience.</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Key Activities:</strong></p><ol><li>Develop and expand B2B relationships with new and existing distributors, brand owners and customers.</li><li>Identify and pursue new sales opportunities across on-trade and off-trade channels and support company’s strategic expansion plans.</li><li>Work closely with distributors, brand owners, customers and internal teams to support trade shows, campaigns, networking events, product launches, and tasting events.</li><li>Ensure client satisfaction and resolve issues related to product delivery, quality, or service.</li><li>Monitor and analyze market trends, competitor activities, sales data and customer feedback to support business planning and strategy development.</li><li>Plan and manage budgets and resources effectively.</li><li>Prepare business proposals, presentations, and reports for internal and external stakeholders.</li><li>Undertake any other ad-hoc responsibilities and duties assigned by the management.</li></ol><p><br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Business, Marketing, Hospitality, or related field.</li><li>WSET or equivalent certification in wine /spirits (preferred).</li><li>Min 2 years of experience in business development or sales, preferably within the <strong>beer, wine, spirits, or F&B or FMCG </strong>sectors.</li><li>Organised, meticulous and resourceful.</li><li><strong>Passionate and knowledge of wine and alcoholic beverage and strong drive for business growth and innovation</strong>.</li><li>Excellent communication (verbal and written), presentation, and negotiation skills.</li><li>Experience in premium brand distribution or channel development is an advantage.</li><li>Willing to travel and work closely with cross-functional teams.</li><li>Ability to handle ad hoc tasks and prioritize responsibilities effectively.</li><li><em>Candidates with more experience may be considered for a Senior Business Development Executive role.</em></li></ul><p>*Our current office is located in Yishun area. Candidate should be willing to relocate to Woodlands area around the end of the 2025.</p>",
